You can use the `typeof` keyword to tell the type system that you know the actual type of the value. Here's an example:

```typescript
// A value that could theoretically be one of multiple values
const value: string | number | boolean;

// The actual value that we know will only be one of these types
const realValue: string = "hello world";

// Use typeof to tell the type system the actual type of the value
const valueIsString: boolean = typeof value === "string";
const valueIsNumber: boolean = typeof value === "number";
const valueIsBoolean: boolean = typeof value === "boolean";

