To draw a board in LaTeX, you can use the `chessboard` package. Here's an example of how to use this package to draw a board in LaTeX:

```
\documentclass{article}

% Load the chessboard package
\usepackage{chessboard}

% Define a function to generate the FEN notation
\newcommand{\fen}[2]{
  \chessboard[#1]{
    #2
  }
}

% Generate a board using the FEN notation
\begin{document}
  \fen{width=1.5cm, height=0.5cm, linewidth=0.5mm, boardcolor=gray!30, color=white}{2kr3/p4pp2/2p3p1}
\end{document}
```

This example generates a board with the FEN notation `2kr3/p4pp2/2p3p1`. The `width` and `height` options are used to specify the size of the board in LaTeX. The `linewidth`, `boardcolor`, and `color` options are used to customize the appearance of the board.

